M|Heur|tx|1. **Representativeness** — Judge probability by similarity to stereotype, ignoring base rates
M|Heur|tx|2. **Availability** — Judge likelihood by ease of recall, ignoring statistical evidence
M|Heur|tx|3. **Anchoring** — Rely heavily on first piece of information received
M|Deci|tx|4. **Framing Effect** — Same outcome, different presentation = different choice
M|Deci|tx|5. **Loss Aversion** — Losses hurt 2x more than gains feel good
M|Deci|tx|6. **Status Quo Bias** — Preference for current state w/o al
